<p>I tried to combine jquery mobile touchstart and touchend with audio record from Cordova. </p>  <p>When a button calls the touchstart event, then it will trigger mediaRect.startRecord(), and when the finger lifts off the screen, it will calls the touchend event which triggers the mediaRect.stopRecord() to stop the audio recording. </p>  <p>On Android 4.4 and below. Whenever the touchstart event triggers the recording, the touchend event wont fire, if i remove the mediaRect.startRecord(); then the touchend fires just fine. </p>  <p>If i use 2 separate buttons for start and stop, the mediaRect.startRecord() and stopRecord() also fires fine. </p>  <p>But when i combine them, i have to trigger the touchstart twice before the touchend will fire. Not sure why. </p>  <pre><code>  $("#record").on('touchstart', function(e){     e.preventDefault();                            mediaRec.startRecord();                      })         $("#record").on('vmousedown', function(e){                                  navigator.notification.vibrate(100);       })   $("#record").on('touchend', function(e){   mediaRec.stopRecord(); }) </code></pre>